    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <h3>What is this website?</h3>
      <div class="answerbox">
        <p>
          This is an original and friendly question-and-answer website. 
          To be part of the community, you just need to create an account. 
          However, there is nothing to worry about: everything on this website is completely free and always will be. 
          To create an account, <a href="login">click here</a>, it is simple to do and very fast! 
          Only an email address, a password and a username is required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3>What questions can I ask?</h3>
      <div class="answerbox">
        <p>
          This website is specialized for programming in general. 
          Anyone can ask about anything related to those topics!
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3>Who answers the questions?</h3> 
      <div class="answerbox">
        <p>Anyone is welcomed to answer the questions and share their knowledge, but they must first register.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>What are those numbers and arrows on the right of the questions and answers?</h3> 
      <div class="answerbox">
        <p>
          This is a voting system. 
          Sometimes, people post very good and interesting questions or solutions and they should get rewarded. 
          This is where the voting system is taken into consideration. 
          As a user, you have the power to upvote the most helpful questions/answers while to downvote those that are biased or unnecessary.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3>Who are you guys, anyway? Do I have any way to contact you?</h3>
        <div class="answerbox">
        <p>We are the creators of this website, and sure you can! Here is our contact information:</p>
